{
  "stem": "21626.3",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "She had the advantage of having a first-class education right from the start, but the disadvantage of not having a loving family like I did who actually chose her.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "She made friends very quickly, particularly with two girls, and spent her holidays with them.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And they also had me during holidays as well so that we could be together as I used to come to the Rainfords, and I used to come-- or to the Campions when I was with there first.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And you know, I used to come and join her.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And in fact, before I went, ever went into the Czech school, I joined her in her boarding school, which was like something out of a fairy tale, beautiful buildings.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "They even had their own lake.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And I remember it was January.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "It was in the winter.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And we were skating on the lake, you know.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And of course, being a Czech, I was, I was brought up on skating and skiing.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And, and to have my sister there and all these lovely girls in their uniform, and-- oh, I hated leaving.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "I spent a fortnight there, and I wished I could stay with her.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "On the other hand, of course, once I got to the Czech school, then I realized what happiness in exile meant, because I was surrounded by kids, as I said, who shared my predicament.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "My teachers, who knew what it was, what the war meant for children like myself, they were more like caring relatives.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "We were like a large, extended family.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And the ties we forged there during those three and a half years have remained stronger, you know, throughout the years.",
      "word_count": 21
    }
  ],
